--- Test Coverage ---
Unit tests (no infrastructure needed):
- TestSetRiskPipeline: verifies SetRiskPipeline stores the pipeline (nil → non-nil)
- TestRiskPipeline_Reject: mock pipeline returns Allowed=false → PlaceOrder returns error "risk rejected at hardlimit: jurisdiction restricted"
- TestRiskPipeline_Allowed: mock pipeline returns Allowed=true with Lots=0.25 → PlaceOrder succeeds, req.Volume overridden to 0.25

Integration tests (require PG + Redis, skipped):
- TestPlaceOrderViaRiskPipeline: full SignalPipeline wired with real components
- TestPlaceOrderViaRiskPipeline_RejectCapability: empty pipeline config → rejected with "no sizer configured"

--- E2E Scenario (verified by code review) ---
1. User with capability_tier=0 (view-only) calls PlaceOrder → CapabilityStore.Get() returns Tier0ViewOnly → TierCheck() returns Allowed=false → "risk rejected at capability: tier view_only cannot trade"
2. User from country=cu → KycJurisdictionRule.Check() → jurisGate → sanctions check → "risk rejected at hardlimit: jurisdiction restricted"
3. Normal user with valid tier → pipeline passes all stages → VolTargetSizer computes lots based on 1% risk budget → volume overridden → order placed

